  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing Access to Relevant Quality Education and Psychosocial Support to Conflict-Affected Children in the Northwest and Southwest Regions of Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this UNESCO project is to increase school enrolment of crisis-affected children in the Northwest and Southwest regions in Cameroon. With this CERF grant, UNESCO will provide $63,000 in capitation grants to public, private and confessional schools and will construct 20 temporary learning spaces among other activities. The project will last nine months and will benefit 18,070 people including 8,995 girls and 900 persons living with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
